Best Downloader Codes for Firestick/Android TV (Sept. 2025 List)

August 29, 2025 / Streaming Apps & Sites

The following guide lists the best Downloader Codes to install free streaming applications on your Fire TV or Android device.

These short numeric codes provide quick installation of apps without having to insert long URLs that can be misspelled or typed incorrectly.

This includes third-party streaming apps that allow users to watch free movies, TV shows, live channels, sports, and more.

Instead of browsing through third-party app stores like APKTime or Unlinked, you can enter a Downloader code for direct, one-click downloads.

In order to use these codes, you must first install the Downloader App on your device. Downloader can be installed on any device that runs the Android operating system, which includes the Amazon Fire TV Stick or Google/Android TV boxes.

This is a must have tool for side-loading apps not available in the Amazon App Store or Google Play Store.

    How Do Downloader Codes Work?

    Each code is a shortened version of a URL that leads directly to an app’s download link. The AFTVNews URL Shortener, built into the Downloader App, allows users to create these codes for faster app access.

    Keep in mind that Downloader does not host these apps but simply provides a way to install them from third-party sources.

    Before using Downloader Codes, enable Unknown Sources in your device settings to allow installations from outside the app store.

    Whether you’re a beginner or an advanced cord-cutter, Downloader codes simplify the installation process and ensures you have access to a wide range of applications.

    Our reviews team at TROYPOINT listed the best codes based on popularity, app quality, reliability, safety, and feedback from streaming forums like the TROYPOINT Insider.

    Are Downloader Codes Legal?

    Yes, Downloader Codes are legal because they are simply shortened links that direct users to app downloads. However, the legality of the apps you install depends on the content they provide and whether they have proper licensing.

    TROYPOINT recommends using 100% legal and verified streaming apps instead of unverified options. The end-user is responsible for content accessed within unverified applications.

    Are they Safe to Use?

    While some of the codes listed above are pointing to official platforms, the “unverified” apps can contain malware or suspicious files.

    We have scanned all unverified sources using VirusTotal to see how safe they are for use.
